    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix itti_terminate_tasks() not sending termination messages to tasks\n\n### Summary\nThe `itti_terminate_tasks()` function was not properly terminating tasks because the underlying `itti_send_terminate_message()` function was implemented as an empty stub. This caused tasks to never receive the TERMINATE_MESSAGE signal needed for graceful shutdown.\n\nThis fix implements the missing `itti_send_terminate_message()` function to properly broadcast TERMINATE_MESSAGE to all registered tasks, allowing them to exit gracefully.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/ocp_itti/intertask_interface.cpp`: \n  - Implemented `itti_send_terminate_message()` to iterate through all tasks and send TERMINATE_MESSAGE\n  - Added proper message allocation and delivery using existing ITTI infrastructure\n  - Maintained existing behavior in `itti_terminate_tasks()` with improved comments\n\n### Reproduction\nBefore this fix, calling `itti_terminate_tasks()` from any task would return immediately without actually signaling other tasks to terminate. Tasks would continue running indefinitely, leading to:\n\n1. Processes that don't shut down cleanly\n2. Resource leaks from tasks that should have been terminated\n3. Deadlock conditions when the main thread waits for tasks that never receive the termination signal\n\nAfter applying this fix, tasks properly receive TERMINATE_MESSAGE and can execute their termination handlers as shown in files like `openair3/MME_APP/mme_app.c` where they call `itti_exit_task()` upon receiving the message.\n"
}